The paper discusses the use of visual psychophysics to make face recognition algorithms more explainable, which falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) and human-computer interaction (cs.HC) sub-categories. The paper also evaluates the behavior of convolutional neural networks, which is a common topic in machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), and neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE) sub-categories.
